<p>While the first image did make me chuckle, the rest of the article was a bore to read. This is one major problem I have with -J articles, the fact that most of the time I know what the gimmick (joke) is before getting to the description, which then describes the gimmick that I already know, and then maybe an addendum or two showing me the gimmick again (because if it wasn't funny the first time, it has to be funny the second time right?). Basically, having the joke be the punchline without set up or buildup, and then compensation by making the punchline be unnecessary longer.</p>

